	<texsupport href="../Analysis_TeXSupport.xml"/>
	<title>Exercises: New Continuous Functions from Old</title>
	<exercise>
		<problem>
			<para>Explain why the functions below are continuous.</para>
		</problem>
		<part>
			<problem>
				<para><latex>f\from \RNr \to \RNr</latex>, <latex>f(x) = 3x^4 -x^2 + 1</latex></para>
			</problem>
			<approach>
				<solution>
					<para>The function <latex>f</latex> is a polynomial (its degree is <latex>4</latex>). So it is continuous.</para>
				</solution>
			</approach>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem>
				<para><latex>g\from \RNr\to \RNr</latex>, <latex>g(x) = -2x^6 + 3x - 4</latex></para>
			</problem>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem>
				<para><latex>h\from \RNr\to \RNr</latex>, <latex>h(x) = e^2 \cdot t^9 - \pi\cdot t^6 + (\pi^2-e)\cdot t^3 + t - 6</latex></para>
			</problem>
			<approach>
				<solution>
					<para>The function <latex>h</latex> is a polynomial (its degree is <latex>9</latex>). So it is continuous. (No need to worry about problems arising from the coefficients <latex>e^2</latex>, <latex>\pi</latex>, <latex>(\pi^2-e)</latex>. These are just numbers. So we are, indeed, dealing with a polynomial.)</para>
				</solution>
			</approach>
		</part>
	</exercise>
	
	
	
	<exercise>
		<problem>
			<para>Find the maximal subset <latex>D</latex> of <latex>\RNr</latex> on which the expression below determines a function <latex>D\to \RNr</latex>.</para>
		</problem>
		<part>
			<problem><para><latex>\frac{x^2+1}{x-1}</latex></para></problem>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem><para><latex>\frac{2x^3+3}{x^+1}</latex></para></problem>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem><para><latex>\frac{x^6+3x^2}{x^2-x -12}</latex></para></problem>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem><para><latex>\sqrt{x^2}</latex></para></problem>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem><para><latex>\sqrt{t-1}</latex></para></problem>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem><para><latex>\sqrt{t^2-1}</latex></para></problem>
		</part>
		<part>
			<problem><para><latex>\sqrt[3]{t^3-1}</latex></para></problem>
		</part>
	</exercise>
